The numbers are placed on the integer lattice by the usual square‑spiral (Ulam spiral).  
For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
r=\max(|x|,|y|),\qquad t=2r+1,\qquad m=t^{2}.
\]

The value at \((x,y)\) is obtained from the side on which the point lies:

* bottom side \((y=-r)\): \(v = m-(r-x)\)
* left side \((x=-r)\): \(v = m-2r-(y+r)\)
* top side \((y=r)\): \(v = m-4r-(x+r)\)
* right side \((x=r)\): \(v = m-6r-(r-y)\)

(The corner points belong to the preceding side.)

For the number 2026 we first locate it.  
\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx45.0\quad\Longrightarrow\quad r=23\;(2r+1=47),\;m=47^{2}=2209.
\]

Since \(m-2026=183\) and \(183>3(2r)=138\) but \(<4(2r)=184\), 2026 lies on the **right side** (\(x=r\)).  
Indeed its coordinates are \((23,-22)\).

Now compute the eight neighbours:

| neighbour | \((x,y)\) | \(r\) | side | value |
|-----------|----------|------|------|-------|
| (22,-23) | \(r=23\) | bottom | \(2209-(23-22)=2208\) |
| (23,-23) | \(r=23\) | bottom‑right corner | \(2209\) |
| (24,-23) | \(r=24\) | right | \(2401-6·24-(24+23)=2401-144-47=2210\) |
| (22,-22) | \(r=22\) | bottom | \(2025-(22-22)=2025\) |
| (24,-22) | \(r=24\) | right | \(2401-144-(24+22)=2401-144-46=2211\) |
| (22,-21) | \(r=22\) | right | \(2025-6·22-(22+21)=2025-132-43=1850\) |
| (23,-21) | \(r=23\) | right | \(2209-138-(23+21)=2209-138-44=2027\) |
| (24,-21) | \(r=24\) | right | \(2401-144-(24+21)=2401-144-45=2212\) |
| (22,-23) already listed, (22,-22) already, the remaining neighbor is (22,-23) (already) and (22,-22) (already). The eight distinct neighbours are the eight cells listed above; the centre (23,-22) is 2026 itself, so we have the eight correct.

Adding them:

\[
\begin{aligned}
2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212 = 16\,952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

Hence the required sum is  

\[
\boxed{16952}.
\]
